The Papua New GuineaAustralia Mutual Defence Treaty (Tok Pisin: Papua Niugini-Ostrelia Mutual Difens Triti), more commonly known as the Pukpuk Treaty (literally crocodile) is a mutual defence treaty between the Independent State of Papua New Guinea and the Commonwealth of Australia agreed upon by each country in September and October 2025 respectively.
The treaty, yet to be ratified by either country's parliament, will allow PNG citizens to join the Australian Defence Force for an accelerated pathway to Australian citizenship and vice-versa. It will also grant Australia expanded access to a number of Papua New Guinea Defence Force (PNGDF) bases such as Lombrum Naval Base and Port Moresby International Airport. In addition, it will set a mutual-defence framework, requiring consultation from either partner if the other experiences an armed attack.
